---
- **Moz**
- Domain Authority tracking
---
- **Screaming Frog**
- Technical SEO audit
{% /table %}

---

## ⚖️ 12.9 White Hat vs Black Hat SEO

{% table %}
- Type
- Description
- Techniques
---
- **White Hat SEO**
- Ethical and search-engine-approved
- Keyword optimization, quality content, backlinks
---
- **Black Hat SEO**
- Manipulative or unethical practices
- Keyword stuffing, hidden text, link spamming
---
- **Gray Hat SEO**
- Mix of both
- Aggressive tactics with minimal risk
{% /table %}

> **Note:** Search engines penalize black-hat practices severely (e.g., delisting).

---

## 🚀 12.10 The Evolution of SEO Algorithms

Search engine algorithms evolve constantly. Some key Google updates include:

{% table %}
- Algorithm
- Purpose
---
- **Panda (2011)**
- Targets thin or duplicate content
---
- **Penguin (2012)**
- Punishes spammy backlinks
---
- **Hummingbird (2013)**
- Improves understanding of search intent
---
- **RankBrain (2015)**
- Uses AI for ranking refinement
---
- **BERT (2019)**
- Enhances natural language understanding
---
- **Helpful Content Update (2022)**
- Rewards user-focused, original writing
{% /table %}

These updates emphasize **quality, intent, and authenticity** over keyword tricks.

---

